Reasoning: The paper discusses the reliability and comparability of peer review results in the context of research teams at two Belgian universities. The paper also compares the peer review results to outcomes from a citation analysis of publications by the same teams. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as it deals with the organization, management, and retrieval of digital information. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the paper discusses the evaluation of research teams, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper discusses the reliability of peer review, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper compares peer review results to citation analysis, and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper discusses the evaluation of research teams at universities.
